HEADWORD: Pottern
<hw>Pot"tern</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
potters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pottern ore</b></col>, <cd>a species of ore which, from
its aptness to vitrify like the glazing of potter's wares, the miners
call by this name.</cd> <au>Boyle.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pottery</ent>⟦br⟧
